data.text:
Maryland Gov. Parris Glendening, right, and Senate President Thomas V. Mike Miller Jr., D-Prince George's, sign bills at the State House in Annapolis Tuesday, April 10, 2001, a day after the 2001 General Assembly ended. Glendening signed 101 bills, including two strengthening drunk driving laws. (AP Photo/Roberto Borea)
